#!hexa strict
// stdlib/yosys/passes.hexa — core Yosys pass library (CLEAN-ROOM skeleton)
//
// @version 0.0.1-skeleton
// @capabilities [passes, rtlil-transform, opt, flatten, proc, techmap]
// @stability skeleton (rfc_006 §4 module-3 of 7; bodies pending §5 gate)
// @since 2026-05-19
//
// CLEAN-ROOM PROVENANCE (design.md Decision 1 — public-surface clean-room)
//   This module re-derives the *public surface* of Yosys' core pass
//   library by inspection of upstream + manual + pass help-text only.
//   No upstream code is copied. Each pass is a typed RTLIL → RTLIL
//   transformation; the dispatcher in this file routes `hexa yosys
//   pass <name>` to the correct implementation.
//
//   - upstream code     : passes/proc/proc.cc          (proc_*)
//                         passes/opt/opt.cc            (opt_*)
//                         passes/cmds/flatten.cc       (flatten)
//                         passes/techmap/techmap.cc    (techmap)
//                         passes/techmap/extract.cc    (extract)
//                         passes/techmap/dfflibmap.cc  (dfflibmap)
//                         passes/cmds/splitnets.cc     (splitnets)
//                         passes/cmds/hierarchy.cc     (hierarchy)
//                         passes/cmds/synth_generic.cc (synth_generic
//                                                       script driver)
//   - upstream manual   : https://yosyshq.readthedocs.io/projects/yosys/
//                          en/latest/cmd/index.html (per-pass help)
//   - upstream license  : ISC (YosysHQ; LICENSE)
//   - upstream repo     : https://github.com/YosysHQ/yosys
//
// rfc_006 §4: module-3 of 7. Minimum pass set required for SKY130
// synth of comb/rtl/router_d{4,6}.v (rfc_006 §5 gate):
//
//   read_verilog → hierarchy -auto-top → proc → flatten → opt →
//   techmap → opt → dfflibmap -liberty <lib.lib> → abc_map (D18) →
//   opt -fast → write_verilog
//
// Each pass body re-derives the *transformation rule* (e.g. "proc"
// = expand always blocks into sync/comb logic + cell list) from the
// manual + standard textbook references (Kahng/Lienig/Markov/Hu
// "VLSI Physical Design", de Micheli "Synthesis and Optimization of
// Digital Circuits"), NOT from upstream source line patterns.

